= Advanced Systems and Integration =

== Boss and Combat Systems ==
StarScript supports custom boss workflows including:
* Multi-phase boss behavior tied to HP thresholds.
* Story node transitions during boss encounters.
* Arena and consequence-oriented progression hooks.

== Relics and Progression ==
Relic systems can model progression states (for example dormant -> awakened -> corrupted) and tie them to story-driven events and item behavior.

== World and Discovery ==
Story logic can react to exploration and world signals:
* Biomes, structures, regions
* Time/day and weather conditions
* Position and proximity thresholds

== GUI and Presentation ==
Use story node style fields and scene effects for presentation:
* Text speed and placement modes
* Panel and border styling
* Overlays, transitions, and screenshake

== Integration Points ==
Typical Java integration surfaces:
* ''StoryEngine'' for activation/progression
* ''StoryStateManager'' for player state, flags, and variables
* Resource/data loading flow via story loader components

== Performance Guidance ==
* Prefer event-based triggers where possible.
* Keep trigger sets focused to current progression stage.
* Avoid unnecessary per-tick heavy checks.
* Use slot/state APIs instead of ad-hoc persistence.

